# Armith frontend UI / UX

When creating or editing UI in `frontend/`, follow this system so landing, dashboard, flows, and results stay visually coherent.

## Design direction (postmodern / neo-system)

- **Tone**: Confident, editorial, slightly brutalist — not generic “SaaS blue”. Prefer **high contrast**, **hard edges** (small radius), **offset hard shadows**, and **one loud accent** (`pm-accent`) plus a **secondary accent** (`pm-accent-alt`) for highlights only.
- **Typography**: Headlines use **`font-display`** (Syne). Body and UI use **`font-sans`** (IBM Plex Sans). **Uppercase + wide tracking** (`tracking-[0.2em] text-xs`) for meta labels, nav groups, and table headers — never for long paragraphs.
- **Surfaces**: Pages sit on **`bg-pm-paper` / `dark:bg-pm-void`**. Cards and panels use **`bg-pm-surface` / `dark:bg-pm-surface-dark`** with **`border-2 border-pm-ink dark:border-white/15`** and **`shadow-brutal`** (see `index.css`). Avoid mixing unrelated motifs (e.g. heavy glassmorphism on one page and flat gray cards on another).
- **Layout**: Use **`max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`** for primary content; **`flex-1 w-full`** for route bodies inside `Layout` (do not stack a second full viewport background that fights the shell).
- **Motion**: Subtle only (`transition-colors`, short transforms). No busy parallax unless explicitly requested.

## Tokens (Tailwind + CSS)

Prefer semantic **`pm-*`** classes from `tailwind.config.js` / `index.css`:

| Role        | Light                          | Dark                                      |
|------------|--------------------------------|-------------------------------------------|
| Page base  | `bg-pm-paper text-pm-ink`      | `bg-pm-void text-pm-ink-soft`             |
| Panel/card | `bg-pm-surface border-pm-ink`  | `bg-pm-surface-dark border-white/15`      |
| Muted copy | `text-pm-muted`                | same                                      |
| Primary CTA| `bg-pm-accent text-white`      | same                                      |
| Links / 2° | `text-pm-accent` hover underline | `text-pm-accent-alt` where contrast needs it |

Shadcn **`primary`** in `:root` is aligned to the accent — use `<Button>` defaults for primary actions.

## Components

- **Buttons**: Use `components/ui/button.jsx` with `variant` / `size`; override with **`pm-*`** utilities only when necessary (e.g. ghost on dark header).
- **Forms**: Inputs: `border-2 border-pm-ink/20 dark:border-white/20 bg-pm-surface dark:bg-pm-surface-dark rounded-sm focus:ring-2 focus:ring-pm-accent`.
- **Alerts**: Keep semantic colors (red/green/yellow) but use **`border-2`** and **`rounded-sm`** to match panels.
- **Tables**: Header row `font-display text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-pm-muted`; rows `hover:bg-pm-wash/50 dark:hover:bg-white/5`.

## Do / don’t

- **Do** reuse `Layout.jsx` chrome; keep **one** footer and **one** header language.
- **Do** add new marketing or dashboard sections as **`pm-panel`**-style blocks, not new one-off gradients.
- **Don’t** introduce a third font family or rainbow gradients per page.
- **Don’t** use `rounded-2xl` + soft shadow on one screen and `rounded-lg` + flat gray on another for the same hierarchy level.

## i18n

All user-visible strings go through **`react-i18next`** (`t('...')`); add keys to `en.json` and `tr.json`.

## Checklist before merging UI work

1. Light + dark both readable (contrast on `pm-accent` on white/black).
2. Route uses **`flex-1 w-full`** when inside `Layout` (no double `min-h-screen` backgrounds).
3. Headings use **`font-display`**; labels use **uppercase + tracking** sparingly.
4. Cards use **`border-2`** + **`shadow-brutal`** (or documented exception in the PR).
